FBIS4-24873 "drchi107_b_94003" FBIS-CHI-94-107 Daily Report 2 Jun 1994 United States & Canada President Clinton Notifies Congress of Decision To Renew MFN President Clinton Notifies Congress of Decision To Renew MFN OW0206221994 Beijing XINHUA in English 2212 GMT 2 Jun 94 OW0206221994 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Washington, June 2 (XINHUA) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton formally notified the congress Thursday [2 June] of his decision to renew the most-favored-nation trading status for China, a White House official said. The notification was announced in Rome where Clinton is on a visit as part of his eight-day European trip celebrating the 50th anniversary of D-Day. Earlier on May 26, Clinton told a White House news conference in Washington that he had decided to extend China's MFN and was moving to separate the linkage between human rights and MFN renewal. The deadline for the President to send a formal notification to Congress is June 3.
